-------------------------------
* Automating board flashing
-------------------------------

	This is working only on Linux.

	A RL78 microcontroller is embedded on the X5H board and controls the SoC
	boot pins, along with the board power.
	This RL78 microcontroller can receive external commands through an USB
	serial port.
	This setup allows to automatically set the board boot pins and to control
	the board power, giving the ability to the user to use the board in a
	fully remote way : invoking the "sdk_writer" tool will be done like before,
	just without any user intervention on the board itself.

	You can use auto_cmd by settings [auto_cmd_tty] in
	".renesas_bsp_rom_writer.x5h_ironhide" file.

		> vi ${IMAGES}/.renesas_bsp_rom_writer.x5h_ironhide
		...
		[auto_cmd_tty]:/dev/ttyUSBx
		...

	see more detail

		${TOP}/README

Setup:

	Power the board off, then set SW43 pin 8 to ON.

Option: [udev rule]

	Install the udev rule that gives a unique and known name to the RL78
	serial port.

		> sudo cp board/x5h_ironhide/linux/99-renesas-rcar-x5h.rules /lib/udev/rules.d
		> sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
		> sudo udevadm trigger

		> vi ${IMAGES}/.renesas_bsp_rom_writer.x5h_ironhide
		...
		[auto_cmd_tty]:/dev/ttyUSB-x5h-rl78
		...
